{
  "texts": [
    "Indeed, a growing body of literature offers and reflects on responsible design for digital health research 49, interventions [50] [51] [52], and technology development 11.",
    "Expecting technology alone to resolve ethical issues and translate ethics into digital health practice, however, constitutes a considerable oversimplification.",
    "Several participants exhibited strong optimism in technology and algorithms to \"solve ethics\".",
    "While these can be a vital translational force, commentators have warned against reducing ethical problems in technology (e.g., privacy) to techno-solutionism, the belief that technology alone will adequately solve major societal and political problems 53.",
    "As stated by Borg 16 \"technical ethical AI tools are necessary, even if insufficient, for addressing the ethical issues AI poses\"."
  ]
}